FAQ_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Get answers to common questions about using our camera app
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_1: What features does the camera app offer?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_1: Our camera app provides a range of features to enhance your photography experience. You can adjust settings like exposure, white balance, and focus. There are also filters, editing tools, and the ability to shoot in different modes like panorama, burst, and slow motion.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_2: How do I access the different camera modes?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_2: To access the different shooting modes, tap the mode icon at the bottom of the camera screen. This will show you options like Photo, Video, Panorama, Portrait, and more. Select the mode you want to use.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_3: Can I edit photos directly in the app?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_3: Yes, our app has a built-in photo editor with tools for cropping, adjusting brightness/contrast, applying filters, and more. Just tap the edit icon after taking a photo to access the editing suite.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_4: How do I change camera settings like resolution and aspect ratio?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: Tap the settings icon in the camera app. This will open a menu where you can adjust resolution, aspect ratio, grid lines, location tagging, and other camera preferences to your liking.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_5: How do I share photos from the app?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_5: After taking or editing a photo, tap the share icon. This will allow you to share the image directly to social media apps, messaging apps, cloud storage services, and more installed on your device.
